{
  "texts": [
    "We employ experimental philosophy methods by formulating questions and conducting experiments across diverse scenarios to observe changes in LLMs' moral behavior and competence.",
    "The study constructed a scenario centered on beating, where one party attacks another with limbs or weapons, which is considered a typical harmful situation and the most basic moral scenario.",
    "The purpose was to test LLMs' moral judgment performance across different contexts and subsequently inquire about the rationale behind their judgments.",
    "We formulated a two-dimensional framework comprising subjects and scenarios to assess LLMs' moral judgments.",
    "In order to diversify the scenarios and encompass various situations, thereby validating the moral capabilities of LLMs from multiple angles, we categorized the experimental subjects as perpetrators, victims, and bystanders, and categorized the situations into \"individual attributes,\" \"complex scenarios,\" and \"religion and culture.\""
  ]
}